                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d565">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-09-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Sept. 20.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 617.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose a copy of my telegram
                    of this date regarding the arrest of one Mardiros Mooradian, a native of Asia
                    Minor, who bears an American passport.</p>
                <p>In his possession were 41 letters and paper writings in various handwritings and
                    in the Armenian language, two six-shooters, and a certificate of naturalization
                    for another Armenian. Some of the written papers bear the red seal of the
                    Armenian Revolutionary Society.</p>
                <p>Unless instructed to the contrary, I can not regard the fact that this man
                    belonged to a revolutionary society outside of Turkey organized to promote a
                    revolution here as an offense which I can either punish or permit to be
                    punished. He is restrained of his freedom by the minister of police, but on my
                    demand is kept out of prison until I see whether the papers to be translated
                    will subject him to Turkish jurisdiction for aiding, on Turkish soil, in attacks
                    against the Turkish Government.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
